======================================================================

Exponent sums for exceptional types:
  G₂: Σm_i = 6, rank = 2, #pos.roots = 6, dim = 14
    Check: rank · h/2 = 2·6/2 = 6 = Σm_i ✓
  F₄: Σm_i = 24, rank = 4, #pos.roots = 24, dim = 52
    Check: rank · h/2 = 4·12/2 = 24 = Σm_i ✓
  E₆: Σm_i = 36, rank = 6, #pos.roots = 36, dim = 78
    Check: rank · h/2 = 6·12/2 = 36 = Σm_i ✓
  E₇: Σm_i = 63, rank = 7, #pos.roots = 63, dim = 133
    Check: rank · h/2 = 7·18/2 = 63 = Σm_i ✓
  E₈: Σm_i = 120, rank = 8, #pos.roots = 120, dim = 248
    Check: rank · h/2 = 8·30/2 = 120 = Σm_i ✓

Average exponent = h/2 for all simple Lie algebras:
  This means the 'center of mass' of exponents is always h/2
  In the tournament recurrence, h/2 is the MIDPOINT between
  the symmetric exponents m and h-m

Exponent duality (m ↔ h-m):
  E₆ (h=12): [1, 4, 5, 7, 8, 11]
    h-m:   [1, 4, 5, 7, 8, 11]
    Self-dual: ✓
    Fixed points (m=h/2): []
  E₇ (h=18): [1, 5, 7, 9, 11, 13, 17]
    h-m:   [1, 5, 7, 9, 11, 13, 17]
    Self-dual: ✓
    Fixed points (m=h/2): [9]
  E₈ (h=30): [1, 7, 11, 13, 17, 19, 23, 29]
    h-m:   [1, 7, 11, 13, 17, 19, 23, 29]
    Self-dual: ✓
    Fixed points (m=h/2): []

